09/May/16 7:25 PM;tlong;Media server supports IPTC metadata translation:
http://stg-remedia101.ihrcloud.net/v3/url/aHR0cHM6Ly9zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tL3VwbG9hZHMuaGlwY2hhdC5jb20vMzAzMTYvMTk4Mjk4L3Q3SlRxYVZrSmFiS0pjSi9HZXR0eUltYWdlcy04MjQ5NjcyNi5qcGVn?metadata=1

It converts fields from their tag values into string names. This is a legacy PHP mapping for field names to asset data:

{code}
$title_exceptions = array(
    'vendorDisney'     => '2#005',
    'vendorEverett'    => '2#005',
    'vendorSummit'     => '2#005',
    'vendorWarner'     => '2#005',
    'vendorThinkstock' => '2#120'
);

// instruction exceptions
// the following uses OriginalTransmissionReference as instruction
$instruction_exceptions = array(
    'vendorPacific' => '2#103'
);

// default map
$map = array(
    'title'       => '2#105',
    'author'      => '2#080',
    'credit'      => '2#110',
    'keyword'     => '2#025',
    'instruction' => '2#040',
    'caption'     => '2#120',
    'copyright'   => '2#116'
);
{code}

Notice there are also some title overrides based on the publisher of the photo. Hopefully we can use the "source" metadata inside of the image to key on this value. If not, we may have to come up with another solution.

To translate the mapping in the PHP to the string fields used in mediad use this file:
https://github.com/ihr-radioedit-apps/mediaserver/blob/master/iptc/iim.go

01/Jun/16 6:21 PM;tlong;{code}
/**
USE THIS: https://www.npmjs.com/package/rrule

Event Types:
Single
Recurring, Bounded
Recurring, Unbounded

- recurrence on any schedule
- remove single occurance
- edit single occurance
- edit series without replacing removed ocurrances (non schedule data only)
- edit occurance and prevent updates from series (non schedule data only)
*/


interface BaseEvent {
	time_start: int;
	time_end: int;
	name: string;
	description: string;
	type: string;  // FROM a particular application
	data: {[k: string]: any};	
}


// Events
interface Event extends BaseEvent {
	_id: "<auto generated>";
	// Recurring Only
	generated_until: Date;
	rrule?: {
		// Matches options for RRULE config
		freq: enum;
		dstart: Date;
		// ETC
	}
}


// Occurrences
interface Ocurrence extends BaseEvent {
	_id: "<auto generated>";
	event_id: ObjectId() | null;  // References Event
	// This is necessary to filter multi-updates that change title/data to prevent 
	// overriding customized occurrences
	is_customized: boolean;
}
{code}

23/Mar/16 3:30 PM;tlong;Boosting across all types of data is a very complex issue. Full sprint+.

Instead, we can solve the immediate irritation of artist matching by using a compound query with boosting for separate types of matches.

Example
{code}
POST _search
{
   "query": {
      "bool": {
         "should": [
            {
               "term": {
                  "object.name": {
                     "value": "drak",
                     "boost": 2
                  }
               }
            },
            {
               "prefix": {
                  "object.name": {
                     "value": "drak",
                     "boost": 1
                  }
               }
            }
         ]
      }
   }
}
{code}

